{
  "_id": "lotmAbilityR8001",
  "name": "Deductive Threading",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-small-teal.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Baseline (1 Spirituality):</strong> As an action, profile one creature you can see within 60 feet for 1 minute (concentration). Make a Spirituality (Investigation) check contested by the target's passive Deception. On a success, establish a deduction profile. Once per round while the profile persists, when the target makes an attack roll, check, or saving throw, you may use your reaction to impose <strong>-1d4</strong> after the roll but before outcome is confirmed. You also gain advantage on Insight checks against that target for the duration.</p><p><strong>Higher Spend (upcast):</strong></p><ul><li><strong>+1 Spirituality:</strong> Profile up to two creatures in range (separate contested checks).</li><li><strong>+2 Spirituality:</strong> Penalty die increases to <strong>-1d6</strong>; if the profiled target fails an Intelligence save against your spell save DC, it cannot take reactions until the start of its next turn.</li><li><strong>+4 Spirituality:</strong> For the first two rounds, you may apply the penalty once each round without spending your reaction.</li></ul><p><em>Counterplay:</em> Breaking line of sight for a full round or masking intent with anti-divination effects ends the profile early.</p><p><em>Corruption Hook:</em> If you use this ability to deliberately frame an innocent target with fabricated logic, gain 1 Corruption.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
